==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Surbase
<hw>Sur"base`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>sur-</ets> + <ets>base</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>A cornice, or series of moldings, on the top of the base of a
pedestal, podium, etc. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Column</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A board or group of moldings running round a room on
a level with the tops of the chair backs.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Surbased</ent>⟦br⟧
